==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Satiety
<hw>Sa*ti"e*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>satietas</ets>, from <ets>satis</ets>, <ets>sat</ets>, enough: cf.
F. <ets>sati⟦eacute⟧t⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>The state of being
satiated or glutted; fullness of gratification, either of the appetite
or of any sensual desire; fullness beyond desire; an excess of
gratification which excites wearisomeness or loathing; repletion;
satiation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In all pleasures there is <qex>satiety</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Hakewill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But thy words, with grace divine⟦br⟧
Imbued, bring to their sweetness no <qex>satiety</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Repletion; satiation; surfeit;
cloyment.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1278 pr=PCP --></p>

<p><ent>Satin</ent>⟦br⟧
